is it possible to sort a es6 map object?  is it possible to sort the entries of a es6 map object? ``` var map = new map();  map.set('2-1', foo);  map.set('0-1', bar); ```  results in:  ``` map.entries = {      0: {"2-1", foo },      1: {"0-1", bar }  } ```  is it possible to sort the entries based on their keys?  ``` map.entries = {      0: {"0-1", bar },      1: {"2-1", foo }  } ``` is it possible to sort a es6 map object?  is it possible to sort the entries of a es6 map object? ``` var map = new map();  map.set('2-1', foo);  map.set('0-1', bar); ```  results in:  ``` map.entries = {      0: {"2-1", foo },      1: {"0-1", bar }  } ```  is it possible to sort the entries based on their keys?  ``` map.entries = {      0: {"0-1", bar },      1: {"2-1", foo }  } ``` yes, it is possible to sort the entries of an es6 map object—but not directly on the map itself since map objects maintain insertion order and do not have built-in sorting methods. however, you can achieve sorted entries by converting the map to an array, sorting it, and then (if desired) creating a new map from the sorted array.

here’s how you can do it:

suppose you have the following map:

```js
var map = new map();
map.set('2-1', foo);
map.set('0-1', bar);
```

