enqueue javascript with type="module"  i want to use `countup.js` on my custom theme in wordpress.  when i add the file with `wp_enqueue_script()`, i get an error:  ``` uncaught syntaxerror: unexpected token 'export' ```  i've read that it can be fixed by setting `type="module"` on the `<script>` tag, but i don't know how to do that as that option doesn't exist in `wp_enqueue_script()`...  can anyone help me? enqueue javascript with type="module"  i want to use `countup.js` on my custom theme in wordpress.  when i add the file with `wp_enqueue_script()`, i get an error:  ``` uncaught syntaxerror: unexpected token 'export' ```  i've read that it can be fixed by setting `type="module"` on the `<script>` tag, but i don't know how to do that as that option doesn't exist in `wp_enqueue_script()`...  can anyone help me? when adding modern javascript libraries like countup.js that use es6 modules (and make use of import/export statements) to your wordpress theme, you may encounter an error like uncaught syntaxerror: unexpected token 'export'. this happens because by default, wordpress adds scripts using a standard <script> tag, without the type="module" attribute that's required for es6 modules.

